{
  "text": "38 improved the original N09 protocol by providing analogous counterfactual protocol with higher frequency. In the same year, Avella et al. experimentally implemented GV protocol [CITATION_1] . To the best of our knowledge this was the first ever experimental demonstration of orthogonal-statebased protocol of QKD. 2011: Experimental realization of N09 protocol was reported shortly after realization of GV protocol. Precisely, in 2011, Ren et al. reported experimental realization of N09 protocol [CITATION_2] . 2012: Soon after Ren et al.'s work two more groups reported experimental realization of N09 protocol. Specifically, Brida et al. [CITATION_3] and Liu et al. [CITATION_4] , independently implemented this protocol of counterfactual quantum communication. In theoretical front, some of the present authors generalized the single particle GV protocol to multipartite case [CITATION_5] and showed that GVtype protocol can be used for secure direct communication and established that while in GV the encoding states are perfectly indistinguishable, in the bi-partite case, they are partially distinguishable, leading to a qualitatively different kind of information-vs-disturbance trade-off and also options for Eve in the two cases. Further, generalizing the idea we had also established that GV-type protocol of DSQC, QSDC and QKD can be realized using arbitrary quantum states [CITATION_6] . Essential ideas that lead to these multipartite GV-type protocols will be explained briefly in the next section. 2013: While the above counterfactual protocols are probabilistic, H. Salih et al.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "119258370",
    "[CITATION_2]": "119181310",
